<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
  xmlns:metal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/metal"
  xmlns:tal="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/tal"
  xmlns:i18n="http://xml.zope.org/namespaces/i18n" i18n:domain="DocentIMS.ActionItems" metal:use-macro="context/main_template/macros/master">
  <body>
    <metal:content-core fill-slot="content">
      <metal:block define-macro="content">

        <h1>Permission & Workflow Audit</h1>
        <div class="lead Description">
          <p>
            <b>Explanation of Permissions, Security and Workflow</b>
          </p>
          <p>First, permissions and workflow are not the same as "Security".  A real-world example using your home will help explain the difference.</p>

          <p><b>Security:</b>  Security is ensuring only invited guests can access your home.  Security is enforced through devices (e.g. locks, security systems, dog, etc.) to create barriers to uninvtied guests. This protects your family and contents from people who should not be in your home.  For Docent IMS, security is controlled by the the technical support team using the tools within Plone.  </p>
          <p><b>Permissions:</b>  Once a user has entered the your home, permissions take over.  Permissions for your home (e.g. change the temperature setting, access the wireless) are assigned to project team members and define which of team members can manage the functioning of the site using actions controled by permissions.  It should be comforting to know, nothing done with permissions (at least those accesible to the Project Manager) can diminish the security of a site.  </p>
          <p><b>Workflow:</b> a workflow is basically the set of steps content goes through from being created to being published. Or, think of it as a "to-do list" with checkpoints that content must pass before it’s visible to the public. As a project manager, this ensures no one sees any content before it has passed through all the steps (perhaps including QC)</p>
        </div>
        
        <form method="get">
          <label>User IDs:</label>
          <br />

          <input id="users" name="users" class="pat-select2 margin-10-0" value="${view/request/users|None}" type="hidden" data-pat-select2='{
                  "placeholder": "Search for users",
                  "width": "40em",
                  "separator": ",",
                  "vocabularyUrl": "${view/portal_url}/@@getVocabulary?name=plone.app.vocabularies.Users"}' />

          <br />
          <label>Folder to audit (e.g. Documents or Meetings):</label>
          <br />

          <select tal:define="selected view/request/folder|view/folder_uid" id="folder" name="folder" class="pat-select2" data-pat-select2="width:20em;">
            <option value=""></option>
            <option tal:repeat="folder view/folders" tal:attributes="selected python: folder['uid'] == selected" value="${folder/uid}">
                ${folder/text}
            </option>
          </select>

          <br />
          <input type="submit" class="btn btn-primary margin-10-0" value="Run Audit"/>
          <a href="${view/portal_url}" class="btn btn-secondary margin-10-0">Exit</a>
        </form>
        <p></p>

        <tal:block tal:condition="view/get_users|None">

          <tal:block tal:condition="view/get_results|None">

            <table tal:define="results view/get_results|None" class="sortable plone-pat-tablesorter pat-tablesorter listing table-bordered">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Path&nbsp;&&nbsp;Icon</th>
                  <th class="main-td">Content Item</th>
                  <th>Type</th>
                  <!-- <th>Path</th>                 -->
                  <th>View</th>
                  <th>Modify</th>
                  <th>Delete</th>
                  <th>Workflow<br/>
Actions</th>
                  <th>Other Permissions</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tal:loop tal:repeat="row results">
                  <tr tal:define="portal_type row/portal_type" tal:condition="python: portal_type != 'Plone Site'">
                    <td tal:define="indent row/indent">
                      <span tal:repeat="dot python:range(indent)" class="smallicon">→</span>
                      <img alt="icon" src="${view/portal_url}/${row/ikon}" />
                    </td>
                    <td class="main-td">
                      <a href="${row/url|None}">
                        <span class="type-${portal_type}">${row/title}</span>
                      </a>
                    </td>
                    <td>   
                       ${portal_type}
                    </td>
                    <tal:define tal:define="users view/get_users">
                      <td>
                        <tal:block tal:repeat="user users">
                          <p tal:define="perms row/users; user python:user" tal:attributes="class python:'yes' if perms and perms[user]['View'] else 'no'">
                          ${python: perms[user]['name']} <span tal:content="python:'✔' if perms and perms[user]['View'] else '✘'" />
                          </p>

                        </tal:block>
                      </td>
                      <td>
                        <tal:block tal:repeat="user users">
                          <p tal:define="perms row/users; user python:user" tal:attributes="class python:'yes' if perms and perms[user]['Modify'] else 'no'">
                          ${python: perms[user]['name']} <span tal:content="python:'✔' if perms and perms[user]['Modify'] else '✘'" />
                          </p>
                        </tal:block>
                      </td>
                      <td>
                        <tal:block tal:repeat="user users">
                          <p tal:define="perms row/users; user python:user" tal:attributes="class python:'yes' if perms and perms[user]['Delete'] else 'no'">
                          ${python: perms[user]['name']} <span tal:content="python:'✔' if perms and perms[user]['Delete'] else '✘'" />
                          </p>
                        </tal:block>
                        <td>
                          <tal:block tal:repeat="user users">
                            <p tal:define="perms row/users; user python:user">
                              <tal:cond tal:condition="perms">
                          ${python: perms[user]['name']}<br/>
                              <span tal:repeat="action python: perms[user]['workflow_actions']" class="action">

                                <b>[${action/title}]</b>
                              </span>
                            </tal:cond>
                          </p>
                        </tal:block>
                      </td>
                      <td>
                        <tal:block tal:repeat="user users">
                          <div tal:define="perms row/users; user python:user">
                            <p>
                              <a href="#user-${repeat/user/index}" class="plone-btn plone-btn-large plone-btn-primary pat-plone-modal">${python: perms[user]['name']}</a>
                            </p>
                            <div id="user-${repeat/user/index}" style="display: none">
                              <h6>${python: perms[user]['name']}</h6>
                              <ul tal:define="other_permissions python:perms[user]['permissions']">
                                <li tal:condition="python: other_permissions[0]">Add Folders</li>
                                <li tal:condition="python: other_permissions[1]">Copy or Move</li>
                                <li tal:condition="python: other_permissions[2]">Change Permissionse</li>
                                <li tal:condition="python: other_permissions[3]">Define Permissions</li>

                              </ul>
                            </div>
                          </div>
                        </tal:block>
                      </td>

                    </tal:define>
                  </tr>
                </tal:loop>
              </tbody>
            </table>
            <script type="text/javascript" src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/tablesorter@2.32.0/dist/js/jquery.tablesorter.min.js"></script>
            <script>
              $(function(){
                $('table.sortable').tablesorter({ });
              });
            </script>

            <style>
        table { border-collapse: collapse; width: 100%; }
        tr:nth-child(even) {background: white} 
        .main-td { text-align: left}
        th, td {text-align: center; }
        th:first-child, td:first-child { text-align: left; }
        th { background-color: #f2f2f2; }
        .smallicon {font-size: 65%}
        .yes { color: green; xfont-weight: bold; }
        .no { color: red; }
        .margin-10-0 {margin: 10px 0;}
        .tablesorter-header.tablesorter-headerAsc { background:whitesmoke; }
        .tablesorter-header.tablesorter-headerDesc { background:#EEE; }
            </style>

          </tal:block>
        </tal:block>
      </metal:block>

    </metal:content-core>
  </body>
</html>
